comments.body:
Thanks [~jianhe] for the patch. I am reviewing your patch, and some initiative comments below. More comments may come later.
{code}
-  public static final int DEFAULT_RESOURCEMANAGER_CONNECT_MAX_WAIT_MS =
+  public static final long DEFAULT_RESOURCEMANAGER_CONNECT_MAX_WAIT_MS =
       15 * 60 * 1000;
+  public static final int DEFAULT_CLIENT_NM_CONNECT_MAX_WAIT_MS =
+      15 * 60 * 1000;
+  public static final long DEFAULT_CLIENT_NM_CONNECT_RETRY_INTERVAL_MS
+      = 10 * 1000;
{code}
I think it is better to keep consistent to use int or long for time intervals or wait. IMO, int should be fine enough as it supports up to (2 ^ 31) millseconds ~ 50 days.

{code}
-    //TO DO: after HADOOP-9576,  IOException can be changed to EOFException
-    exceptionToPolicyMap.put(IOException.class, retryPolicy);
{code}
Do we have plan to get HADOOP-9576 in? If yes, shall we keep the todo comments here?

